        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 3:50PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Darden, or 7 miles southeast of Natchez Trace State Forest, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Camden, Parsons, Decaturville, Darden, Scotts Hill, Perryville,
Busseltown, Jeannette, Warrens Bluff, Wilkinstown, I-40 Near The
Tennessee River, Haney, Rock Hill, Holladay, Mount Tabor, Garrett,
Sugar Tree, Beacon, Hickory Forks, and Largo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
